Still, the slugger's story is filled with tragedy, as cocaine helps ruin what might have been a Hall of Fame career. The Straw Man's life in and out of the game has been littered with suspensions, probation and stints in prison, in drug treatment facilities and under house arrest. Most notably, Strawberry serves nearly a year in prison starting in 2002 after violating his probation on a 1999 conviction for drug and solicitation of prostitution charges.
